This paper deals with natural language processing techniques applied to electronic health records, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of concept embeddings, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions measuring divergences in concept usage, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with analyzing semantic characteristics of clinical document collections, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
